./CHANGELOG.md:181:- The `ErrorType` function in `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/semconv/v1.37.0` now handles custom error types.
./CHANGELOG.md:182:  If an error implements an `ErrorType() string` method, the return value of that method will be used as the error type. (#7442)
./CHANGELOG.md:244:- Add `ErrorType` attribute helper function to the `go.opentelmetry.io/otel/semconv/v1.34.0` package. (#6962)
./CHANGELOG.md:512:- Global MeterProvider registration unwraps global instrument Observers, the undocumented Unwrap() methods are now private. (#5881)
./CHANGELOG.md:542:- Performance improvements for the trace SDK `AddEvent`, `AddLink`, `RecordError` and `End` methods in `Span`. (#5874)
./CHANGELOG.md:1482:  Existing users of the exporters attempting to identify specific errors will need to use `errors.Unwrap()` to get the underlying error. (#3516)
./CHANGELOG.md:2130:- Added `"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/trace".WithStackTrace` option to add a stack trace when using `span.RecordError` or when panic is handled in `span.End`. (#2163)
./CHANGELOG.md:2419:- Span `RecordError` now records an `exception` event to comply with the semantic convention specification. (#1492)
./CHANGELOG.md:2515:- Removed setting status to `Error` while recording an error as a span event in `RecordError`. (#1663)
./CHANGELOG.md:2710:- The function signature of the Span `RecordError` method in `go.opentelemetry.io/otel` is updated to no longer take an unused context and instead take a required error value and a variable number of `EventOption`s. (#1254)
./CHANGELOG.md:3381:- `RecordError` method on `Span`s in the trace API to Simplify adding error events to spans. (#473)
